pullsbody:
https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=744581

Creates a page for users to view all snippets that are currently available from the snippets service.

A few notes:
- `<script>` and `<style>` tags are intentionally left in, as they often are integral to the snippet preview. In the future we might escape or remove these if any issues arise.
- There are no tests for the view; it's simple enough currently.
pull_repo_desc: simple content manager for Fx4 home page snippets
pull_commit_message: Add page to view all currently active snippets.

pulltitle: Add <div> around all snippets with their snippet ID
pullsbody:
In order to write JS that automatically tracks snippet impressions, we need a way to get the ID of a snippet via JS. This surrounding div lets us grab the ID and send that off to the impressions service when the snippet is viewed.

Tested on the new and old about:home page, this extra div does not affect how snippets appear visually.
pull_repo_desc: simple content manager for Fx4 home page snippets
pull_commit_message: Add <div> around all snippets with their ID.

pulltitle: Refactor snippet editor and save snippet icon url.
pullsbody:
Switches to using ICanHaz for JS templating and reorganizes the
snippet editor to be a bit more manageable.

In addition, the snippet editor saves the icon URL in a comment
in the snippet so the url box keeps the icon URL between saves.
pull_repo_desc: simple content manager for Fx4 home page snippets
pull_commit_message:
Refactor snippet editor and save snippet icon url.

Switches to using ICanHaz for JS templating and reorganizes the
snippet editor to be a bit more manageable.

In addition, the snippet editor saves the icon URL in a comment
in the snippet so the url box keeps the icon URL between saves.

pullsbody:
Changes client match rules such that any inclusion rule that doesn't match a client causes the associated snippet to not be sent to the client. 

This lets us scale by using a small set of rules and composing them together on snippets to limit which clients get which snippets.
pull_repo_desc: simple content manager for Fx4 home page snippets
pull_commit_message:
Change so inclusion rules on a snippet that don't
match stop the snippet from being sent to the user
